      • placeDie

        public boolean placeDie(Die d,
                        int row,
                        int column,
                        boolean colorRestriction,
                        boolean valueRestriction,
                        boolean placementRestriction)
        edit @danmontesi placeDie will return boolean instead of void for usability. In this way, if it returns true (= correct placement), automatically modify permanently the model and call next Turn if it returns false (= incorrect placement), model doesn't change and i will be able to notify the view of the incorrect move and restart the player's turn
        Parameters:
        d - to be placed die
        row - cell row number
        column - cell column number
        colorRestriction - cell color restriction
        valueRestriction - cell value restriction
        placementRestriction - placement restriction
        Returns:
        true if restrictions are respected and die is place, false otherwise
